%% Scalability Tiers -- bottleneck-driven growth path
%% Referenced in: docs/scalability.md
flowchart LR
    T1["100 users<br/>Bottleneck: data loss on restart<br/>Fix: Postgres"]
    T2["1,000 users<br/>Bottleneck: Ollama serializes requests<br/>Fix: vLLM + stateless replicas"]
    T3["100,000 users<br/>Bottleneck: sync HTTP doesn't scale<br/>Fix: async queue, rate limits, read replicas"]
    T4["1,000,000 users<br/>Bottleneck: single-region DB<br/>Fix: sharding, data residency"]
    T5["100,000,000 users<br/>Bottleneck: per-request cost compounds<br/>Fix: model cascading, dedicated infra"]

    T1 -->|new bottleneck appears| T2 -->|new bottleneck appears| T3 -->|new bottleneck appears| T4 -->|new bottleneck appears| T5
